<TITLE> Russia new defence minister may be a woman: general </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MOSCOW, Sept 19 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A woman could be appointed as Russia's new defence minister in a move that would break centuries of male dominance in the highly conservative armed forces, Russia's top general said on Wednesday. Defence Minister Anatoly Serdyukov has submitted his resignation to President Vladimir Putin because of close family ties to Prime Minister Viktor Zubkov. Serdyukov is married to Zubkov's daughter. Russia's chief of the general staff, Yuri Baluyevsky, told reporters that the next minister should be a civilian and that a woman could be appointed to the post. "Could we take the example of several countries and invite a woman to the post of minister?" Baluyevsky was quoted as asking. "I do not rule out that a woman could become our minister," Interfax news agency reported. "The main function of the minister is that the soldiers are fed and that they have new tanks," he said. Russia has never had a female defence minister. The Izvestia newspaper said possible candidates for the post are Lyubov Kudelina, a deputy defence minister who deals with financial questions, Nikolai Pankov, another defence minister, or Baluyevsky himse
